<?php
/* Security release? */
$notes['security'] = false;

/* Mailing list release notes. */
$notes['changes'] = <<<ML
The Horde Team is pleased to announce the final release of the Horde Groupware
Webmail Edition version 5.2.13.

Horde Groupware Webmail Edition is a free, enterprise ready, browser based
communication suite. Users can read, send and organize email messages with four
different webmail interfaces and manage and share calendars, contacts, tasks,
notes, files, and bookmarks with the standards compliant components from the
Horde Project.

For upgrading instructions, please see
http://www.horde.org/apps/webmail/docs/UPGRADING

For detailed installation and configuration instructions, please see
http://www.horde.org/apps/webmail/docs/INSTALL

Thanks to duarteetraud@gmail.com and Centurion Information Security
(www.centurioninfosec.sg) for reporting the XSS vulnerabilities.

The major changes compared to the Horde Groupware Webmail Edition version
5.2.12 are:

General changes:
    * Update Greek translation.
    * Several bugfixes and improvements.

Address Book changes:
    * Honor alternative_name mapping (Bug #14280).
    * Fix dealing with orphaned virtual address books.

Calendar changes:
    * Fix updating list of resource calendars in resource group dialog (Bug #14281).
    * Fixed several issues with resource management.

Mail changes:
    * Fix opening compose window on IE when uploads are disabled (Bug #14267).
    * Fix creating new trash folder from preference screen.
    * Fix finding reply or forward text from signed or encrypted messages with
      HTML content.

Filter changes:
    * Honor 'date', 'echo', and 'ls' path overrides.
    * Fix Oracle compatibility.
    * Small bugfixes and improvements.

Tasks changes:
    * Honor date_format prefs in Task form (Bug #14287).
ML;

$notes['name'] = 'Horde Groupware Webmail Edition';
$notes['list'] = 'horde';
return $notes;
